Package: libxpc-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libxpc1 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: A portable utility library for C++ libraries.
 The XPC++ library is a cross-platform C++ library.  It is meant for producing
 applications that are easier to write, easier to follow, and easier to
 debug.  This is the header-file package for libxpc++.  The files are
 installed into $prefix/include/xpc-1.1/xpc.
 .
 This package contains the development files.

Package: libxpc1
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A portable utility library for C++ libraries.
 The XPC++ library is a cross-platform C++ library.
 It is meant for supplementing the C library, libxpc, with C++-only 
 functionality.
